　　Jack Henry Quaid (born April 24, 1992)is an American actor, the son of the actors Meg Ryan and Dennis Quaid. His recent films include The Hunger Games and a short film, Sitting Babies. The Hunger Games was his first major role.　　Quaid was born in Los Angeles, California. In April 2011, it was announced that Quaid had been cast as the District One tribute Marvel in the much-anticipated film The Hunger Games.[The movie was released internationally on March 23, 2012.　　He is currently studying Drama at New York University.
